# Event-Driven Adaptive Training System Plan

Moving from an index-based (completed day counts) system to a deterministic, calendar-accurate, event-driven state architecture.

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> This refactor changes how progress is computed. We will replace `UserEvent`-derived counts with a single JSON/Storage-persisted [ProgramState](file:///e:/MyRealTimeProjects/OriginalWorking/FitnessApp/src/features/program/services/programStateEngine.ts#120-226) object. We will also need to introduce a migration function to bootstrap existing active users into this new [ProgramState](file:///e:/MyRealTimeProjects/OriginalWorking/FitnessApp/src/features/program/services/programStateEngine.ts#120-226).

## Proposed Changes

### Core Models & State Architecture
We will introduce strict types defining the [ProgramState](file:///e:/MyRealTimeProjects/OriginalWorking/FitnessApp/src/features/program/services/programStateEngine.ts#120-226) and its unified source of truth.

#### [NEW] `src/core/models/ProgramState.ts`
Establishes the exact target shape of [ProgramState](file:///e:/MyRealTimeProjects/OriginalWorking/FitnessApp/src/features/program/services/programStateEngine.ts#120-226), [Session](file:///e:/MyRealTimeProjects/OriginalWorking/FitnessApp/src/features/program/services/programStateEngine.ts#10-11), and events.
```typescript
export type ProgramPhase = 'FOUNDATION' | 'PROGRESSION' | 'DELOAD';
export type SessionStatus = 'PLANNED' | 'COMPLETED' | 'MISSED' | 'RECOVERY';

export type Session = {
  id: string; // e.g. "week1-day1" or physical UTC date stamp
  planned_date: string; // Physical UTC Date "YYYY-MM-DD"
  status: SessionStatus;
  focus_type: string;
  title: string;
};

export type AdaptationSummary = {
  reason: string;
  change_summary: string;
  load_delta?: number;
  volume_delta?: number;
};

export type ProgramStateEvents = 
  | 'PROGRAM_CREATED'
  | 'SESSION_STARTED'
  | 'SESSION_COMPLETED'
  | 'DAY_MISSED'
  | 'RECOVERY_UPDATED'
  | 'FREQUENCY_CHANGED'
  | 'ONBOARDING_UPDATED';

export interface ProgramState {
  id: string;
  user_id: string;
  training_days_per_week: number;
  preferred_training_days: number[]; // 0=Sun, 1=Mon, etc. (Optional, if applicable)
  program_phase: ProgramPhase;
  sessions: Session[];
  streak: number;
  recovery_state: boolean; // True if today is a recovery day
  last_session_summary: any | null;
  last_adaptation: AdaptationSummary | null;
  
  // Internal counters for continuity
  last_missed_at: string | null;
  consecutive_misses: number;
}
```

---

### Event Engine & Deterministic Resolver

#### [MODIFY] [src/features/program/services/programStateEngine.ts](file:///e:/MyRealTimeProjects/OriginalWorking/FitnessApp/src/features/program/services/programStateEngine.ts)
We completely rewrite [resolveProgramState](file:///e:/MyRealTimeProjects/OriginalWorking/FitnessApp/src/features/program/services/programStateEngine.ts#120-226) to eliminate day indices. Instead of array index logic (`completedCount + 1`), it will iterate through `sessions[]` using pure UTC calendar math.

```typescript
export function resolveNextSession(
  programState: ProgramState, 
  calendarContext: { todayUTC: string, userTimezone: string }
): Session | null {
  // Pure function: Finds first PLANNED session >= today
  // Trigger missed day updates if PLANNED session exists < today
}
```

We evaluate the "Missed Day Engine" explicitly inside the state reducer:
- Auto-detects if `planned_date < today AND status === 'PLANNED'`
- Marks as `MISSED`, schedules recovery, and shifts upcoming PLANNED sessions forward.

We extract the "Streak Engine":
- Completing a planned session -> `streak++`
- `recovery_state === true` -> streak freezes.
- Session marked `MISSED` -> `streak = 0`.

